&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;LOCATION:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;The territory for this position is Knoxville, TN.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;OUR MISSION&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p id=&quot;m_-4453591297383348068gmail-p-rc_703414fdc3cd9241-748&quot;&gt;Natera™ is a global leader in cell-free DNA (cfDNA)&amp;nbsp;testing, dedicated to oncology, women&#39;s health, and organ health. Our aim is to make personalized genetic testing and diagnostics part of the standard of care to protect health and enable earlier and more targeted interventions that lead to longer, healthier lives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;POSITION SUMMARY&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Account Sales Representative (ASR) is a highly driven, competitive, and relationship-focused professional responsible for contributing to account sales, service, and support activities across our clinical product portfolio. This role focuses on maximizing patient retention and test cadence compliance within existing accounts, while strategically deepening our footprint within key medical practices and regional hospital networks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate possesses a high-energy, competitive personality, combined with exceptional organizational habits that ensure no detail or follow-up is missed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PRIMARY RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Establish &amp;amp; Expand Institutional Relationships:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Cultivate, grow, and maintain deep-rooted relationships with physicians, clinical staff, practice managers, and key stakeholders across hospital systems and medical practices within the Knoxville market.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drive Account Retention &amp;amp; Growth:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Work closely with field sales partners to seamlessly support existing customers, ensuring patients adhere to their prescribed test cadence to improve long-term outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;im&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Execute Flawless Follow-Up:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Serve as the primary, reliable point of contact for clinical workflows, test fulfillment, and logistics; follow up rigorously on customer requests and navigate internal systems to resolve friction points quickly.&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Master Territory Time Management:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Assess, prioritize, and structure daily field schedules efficiently to balance high-volume account touchpoints with high-impact strategic tasks.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Leverage Corporate Resources:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Educate medical professionals on the digital tools, educational assets, and patient resources that Natera provides to facilitate seamless test order management.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-Functional Collaboration:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Partner fluidly with internal stakeholders—including&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Clinical Field Specialists (CFSs), Strategic Account Managers (SAMs), Medical Science Liaisons (MSLs)&lt;/strong&gt;, and patient coordinators—to maximize unit growth and deliver elite provider and patient experiences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Utilize Data &amp;amp; Metrics:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Analyze and monitor internal reports of key performance indicators (KPIs) related to patient retention and fulfilled order volume to proactively identify areas of workflow improvement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;QUALIFICATIONS &amp;amp; EXPERIENCE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;im&quot;&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree preferred (or Associate&#39;s degree with a minimum of 4 years of relevant clinical/sales experience).Minimum of 2 years of business-to-business (B2B) or medical sales experience with a proven track record of hitting targets, OR a background as a medical assistant, clinical support, patient liaison, or nurse.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
